  <title>
    <phrase>Open as Layer</phrase>
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
  </title>

  <indexterm significance="normal">
    <primary>Image</primary>
    <secondary>Open</secondary>
    <tertiary>Open as layer</tertiary>
  </indexterm>
  <indexterm significance="normal">
    <primary>Layer</primary>
    <secondary>Stack managing</secondary>
    <tertiary>Open an image as layer</tertiary>
  </indexterm>
  <indexterm significance="normal"><primary>Open as Layer</primary></indexterm>

  
  

  
  
  

  
  
  

  

  
  
  

  

  <para>
    The <guimenu moreinfo="none">Open Image as layer</guimenu> dialog is identical to
    the <link linkend="gimp-file-open">Open Image</link> dialog.  With
    this dialog, you can open an image file, which is added to the current
    image as the top layer in the stack.
  </para>

  

  

  

  

  

  

  

  <sect3>
    <title>
      <phrase>Activate Command</phrase>
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      <!--      <phrase lang="zh_CN">开启对话框</phrase>-->
    </title>

    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          You can access to this command from the image menubar through
          <menuchoice moreinfo="none">
            <guimenu moreinfo="none"><accel>F</accel>ile</guimenu>
            <guimenuitem moreinfo="none">Op<accel>e</accel>n as layer</guimenuitem>
          </menuchoice>,
        </para>
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para>
          or by using the keyboard shortcut
          <keycombo moreinfo="none">
            <keycap moreinfo="none">Ctrl</keycap>
            <keycap moreinfo="none">Alt</keycap>
            <keycap moreinfo="none">O</keycap>
          </keycombo>.
        </para>
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  </sect3>
